  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Slice the <strong>red cabbage</strong> into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> large wedges, keeping the stalks intact so they stay together, trimming away any browned edges</p><p>Top, tail and grate the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>red cabbage wedges</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and sprinkle with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until the stalks of the cabbage are fork-tender – these are your <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>red cabbage wedges</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2455Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the cabbage is cooking, add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 16-18 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is almost cooked with a slight bite (you'll finish cooking it in step 6!)</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and keep covered</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
